<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Cylinder Head And Valves -
        Cylinder Head Assembly - Connecting Under Valve Cover Harness
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Connecting Under Valve Cover Harness</title>
        <figure id="f1200499" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9135.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Valve Cover Gasket</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket With UVC Harness</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector Solenoid Harness Connectors</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow Plug Leads</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the valve cover gasket with the UVC harness onto the cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the electrical leads to the glow plugs by pressing the connector onto the glow
                plugs.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200472" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd09/D0941.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Connecting the Connector to the Fuel Injector Solenoid</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connector</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket Surface</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the fuel injector electrical connector by inserting the connector into the socket.
                Push the connector up and secure it with the metal wire bail.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure all UVC wiring is free and clear of any moving parts and free of possible
                entrapment by the valve cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
